description: Four hostages were rescued over the weekend by Israeli forces, but the families of the remaining hostages in Gaza will “continue to be a source of pressure” on Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, said Ambassador Dennis Ross. “Hamas is probably embarrassed by what happened,” Ross said. “In the immediate aftermath of that, I don’t believe that you’re going to see a greater likelihood of a ceasefire deal being done.”
title: Hamas likely ‘embarrassed’ by fallout from hostage rescue, says former Mideast envoy

description: An Austrian Airlines airplane’s nose and cockpit windows were severely damaged by hail during a flight from Spain to Austria after encountering a thunderstorm cell, officials say.
title: Austrian Airlines plane’s nose, cockpit windows damaged during flight by severe hail storm

description: The White House has discussed the possibility of negotiating a deal directly with Hamas to release the Americans still being held hostage in Gaza. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez reports on the potential that the Biden administration makes a deal with Hamas.
title: Biden administration is discussing a potential Hamas deal to free U.S. hostages

description: French President Emmanuel Macron dissolved the lower house of parliament in a surprise announcement, sending voters back to the polls in just a few weeks' time, after his party was handed a humbling defeat by the far-right in the European elections.
title: Macron shocks France with snap election after far-right gains in European Parliament

description: French President Emmanuel Macron called snap elections after rival Marine le Pen and other far-right figures made gains in the European Parliament.
title: Macron's big gamble to halt the far-right surge in Europe

description: The recent rescue of four hostages will likely complicate U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken’s effort to release the remaining hostages and achieve a cease-fire agreement between Israel and Hamas, according to a senior administration official.
title: Hostage rescue complicates U.S. push for a cease-fire deal

description: Catherine, the Princess of Wales, has apologized for not attending a military parade this weekend, after speculation it could have been be her first public appearance since revealing she was receiving cancer treatment.
title: Princess Kate apologizes for missing military parade amid cancer treatment

description: Eyewitnesses of Israel's hostage rescue operation described scenes of intense violence as residents of Nuseirat surveyed the damage and injured Palestinians received treatment.
title: Eyewitness of Israel's hostage rescue operation tells of indiscriminate killing

description: Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese urged activists on both sides of the Israel-Palestinian debate to “turn the heat down” after the U.S.
title: Australia PM urges activists to ‘turn the heat down’ after U.S. Consulate vandalized over Gaza war

description: U.S. officials have discussed potentially negotiating a unilateral deal with Hamas to secure the release of five Americans being held hostage in Gaza.
title: Biden Administration has discussed potentially negotiating unilateral deal with Hamas to free U.S. hostages

description: Ukrainian forces have for the first time hit a latest-generation Russian Sukhoi Su-57 fighter jet at an air base inside Russia, Kyiv’s GUR defense intelligence agency said on Sunday, showing satellite pictures which it said confirmed the strike.
title: Ukraine says it hit latest-generation Russian fighter jet for the first time

description: Taylor Swift stopped her concert in Edinburgh, Scotland, on Friday to help a fan.
title: Taylor Swift stops mid-song to help a fan in distress at Edinburgh Eras tour show

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's key rival, Benny Gantz, announced that he is quitting the war Cabinet after a postwar plan for the Palestinian enclave failed to materialize.
title: Israeli war cabinet member Benny Gantz announces resignation
